body:
The core feature in this PR is a function `BaseTableDataManager.getStaleSegments` which finds all the segments of a table that are not up to date with the current table config. It accepts a Table Config and Schema and compares that with the current state of a segment. 

This functionality will be used by other components such as minion tasks to decide which segments have to be refreshed. 

The function is exposed by the following server API:

```
/tables/{tableName}/segments/isStale

Response is:
[
  {
     "segmentName":"...",
     "reason":"..."
  },
...
]
```

**segmentName** is the name of the segment.
**reason** contains a simple message for why the segment needs to be refreshed.

There is also a controller API that consolidates the responses from all servers.

```
/segments/orders_OFFLINE/isStale

Response is:
{
  "<server name>" : [{
     "segmentName":"...",
     "reason":"..."
  }],
...
]

Example:

{
  "http://192.168.0.111:7500/tables/orders_OFFLINE/segments/isStale__1": [
    {
      "segmentName": "orders_OFFLINE_0",
      "reason": "column added"
    }
  ]
}
```


Fix for #14450
